  "sw_detailed": {
    "module_name": "GTM_TOM_3_Phase_Inverter_PWM",
    "public_functions": [
      {
        "signature": "void initGtmTom3phInv(void)",
        "behavior_description": "Declare persistent module state (PWM handle, channels array, and arrays for dutyCycles[3], deadTimes[3], phases[3]). Create local configuration objects: IfxGtm_Pwm_Config config; IfxGtm_Pwm_ChannelConfig channelConfig[3]; IfxGtm_Pwm_OutputConfig output[3]; IfxGtm_Pwm_DtmConfig dtmConfig[3]; IfxGtm_Pwm_InterruptConfig interruptConfig. Initialize the main PWM config with defaults using the GTM module SFR. Populate per-channel output configuration for three logical channels (indices 0..2) with complementary outputs: set each output[i].pin to the high-side TOUT, output[i].complementaryPin to the low-side TOUT, set polarity/complementaryPolarity to active-high, outputMode to push-pull, and padDriver to the requested pad driver. Set per-channel deadtime config (rising and falling both to 1 µs) and assign dtmConfig[i] to channelConfig[i]. Assign initial duty in percent to channelConfig[0..2] as 25, 50, 75 respectively; set phase to 0 for all; assign output[i] to channelConfig[i]. Configure interruptConfig with mode set to pulse notify, service provider CPU0, priority 20, and periodEvent pointing to IfxGtm_periodEventFunction; assign channelConfig[0].interrupt = &interruptConfig and channelConfig[1], channelConfig[2] to NULL. Fill main config fields: select TOM submodule on cluster 1, center alignment, enable synchronous start and synchronous updates, set frequency to 20 kHz, select the DTM clock source, set numChannels=3 and channels pointer to channelConfig. Inside a GTM enable guard: if GTM is not enabled, enable it, then read the module frequency dynamically, set GCLK to that frequency, set CLK0 to the same frequency, and enable the FXCLK clocks. Initialize the PWM by calling the high-level init with the persistent channels array. After init, copy initial duties and dead-times into the persistent state arrays for later updates. Finally, configure the LED GPIO pin as output (push-pull) so the ISR can toggle it. Do not perform explicit start calls; syncStart in the config handles starting and synchronization. Do not call any PinMap_set* or low-level TOM/ATOM APIs. Ensure periodEvent uses the void *data function (IfxGtm_periodEventFunction) and is distinct from the ISR.",
        "driver_calls": [
          "IfxGtm_isEnabled",
          "IfxGtm_enable",
          "IfxGtm_Cmu_getModuleFrequency",
          "IfxGtm_Cmu_setGclkFrequency",
          "IfxGtm_Cmu_setClkFrequency",
          "IfxGtm_Cmu_enableClocks",
          "IfxGtm_Pwm_initConfig",
          "IfxGtm_Pwm_init",
          "IfxPort_setPinModeOutput"
        ],
        "from_reference": true,
        "call_context": "init"
      },
      {
        "signature": "void updateGtmTom3phInvDuty(void)",
        "behavior_description": "Read the three duty values (in percent) from module state. For each channel index 0..2: add the fixed step of 10 percent. If any updated duty is greater than or equal to the max limit (90 percent), wrap it to the min limit (10 percent). Store the updated duty values back to state. Apply the changes immediately and synchronously to all three complementary PWM channels by passing the state’s dutyCycles array directly (percent values) to the high-level API for immediate multi-channel duty update. No timing or STM logic is performed here.",
        "driver_calls": [
          "IfxGtm_Pwm_updateChannelsDutyImmediate"
        ],
        "from_reference": true,
        "call_context": "loop"
      },
      {
        "signature": "void interruptGtmAtom(void)",
        "behavior_description": "ISR toggles the LED output pin each time the routed GTM ATOM periodic interrupt fires. Perform only minimal work: toggle the LED pin and return.",
        "driver_calls": [
          "IfxPort_togglePin"
        ],
        "from_reference": false,
        "call_context": "none"
      },
      {
        "signature": "void IfxGtm_periodEventFunction(void *data)",
        "behavior_description": "Empty period-event callback used by the high-level PWM driver. Accepts a void *data parameter; suppress unused-parameter warnings and perform no action.",
        "driver_calls": [],
        "from_reference": false,
        "call_context": "none"
      }
    ],
    "private_functions": [],
    "dependencies": {
      "includes": [
        "Ifx_Types.h",
        "IfxGtm_Pwm.h",
        "IfxPort.h",
        "IfxPort_Pinmap.h"
